{"name":"Slayer (PrC)","type":"class","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/classesraces/slayer.png","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf1.classes.cOY76lMUkupH534m"},"scene-packer":{"hash":"c2f750f900dc8f363407aa5e4ce19c4ed6dba294","sourceId":"Item.omQz6bA65rjFR3Vy"}},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Skilled at tracking down targets, slayers are consummate hunters, living for the chase and the deadly stroke that brings it to a close. Slayers spend most of their time honing their weapon skills, studying the habits and anatomy of foes, and practicing combat maneuvers.</p><p><strong>Role</strong>: The slayer is elusive, and good at finding the opportune time and location to strike. Combining the deadliest talents of rangers and rogues, a slayer’s abilities are all about getting into combat, dealing with a target, and then getting back out again.</p><h2 class=\"title\">Requirements</h2><p>To qualify to become an duelist, a character must fulfill the following criteria.<br><br><strong>Base Attack Bonus:</strong> +4<br><strong>Feats</strong>: Dazzling Display, Exotic Weapon Proficiency (dueling sword), Weapon Finesse, Weapon Focus (dueling sword). <br><strong>Skills</strong>: Knowledge (Nature) 3 ranks, Stealth 5 ranks, and Survival 4 ranks.<br><strong>Special:</strong> Favored Enemy class feature and Sneak Attack +2d6.</p><h2><span id=\"Class_Skills\">Class Skills</span></h2><p>The slayer’s class skills are <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/acrobatics\">Acrobatics</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Dexterity-Dex-\">Dex</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/bluff\">Bluff</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Charisma-Cha-\">Cha</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/climb\">Climb</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Strength-Str-\">Str</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/craft\">Craft</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Int</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/disguise\">Disguise</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Charisma-Cha-\">Cha</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/heal\">Heal</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Wisdom-Wis-\">Wis</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/intimidate\">Intimidate</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Charisma-Cha-\">Cha</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/knowledge\">Knowledge</a> (dungeoneering) (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Int</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/knowledge\">Knowledge</a> (geography) (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Int</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/knowledge\">Knowledge</a> (local) (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Int</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/perception\">Perception</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Wisdom-Wis-\">Wis</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/profession\">Profession</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Wisdom-Wis-\">Wis</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/ride\">Ride</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Dexterity-Dex-\">Dex</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/sense-motive\">Sense Motive</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Wisdom-Wis-\">Wis</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/stealth\">Stealth</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Dexterity-Dex-\">Dex</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/survival\">Survival</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Wisdom-Wis-\">Wis</a>), and <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/swim\">Swim</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Strength-Str-\">Str</a>).</p><p><strong>Skill Ranks per Level</strong>: 6 + <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Int</a> <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Determine-Bonuses\">modifier</a>.<br><strong>Hit Die</strong>: d10.</p><h2 class=\"title\">Class Features</h2><table class=\"inner\" style=\"width: 96.9314%;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\"><strong>Level</strong></td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\"><strong>Base Attack Bonus</strong></td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\"><strong>Fort Save</strong></td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\"><strong>Ref Save</strong></td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\"><strong>Will Save</strong></td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\"><strong>Special</strong></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">1st</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+0</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Studied Target</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">2nd</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Slayer Talent, Sneak Attack +1d6</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">3rd</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Stalker</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">4th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+4</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Slayer Talent, Sneak Attack +2d6</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">5th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+5</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">2nd Studied Target</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">6th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+6</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Advanced Talents, Slayer Talent</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">7th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+7</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+4</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+4</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Sneak Attack +3d6</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">8th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+8</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+4</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+4</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Slayer Talent</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">9th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+9</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+5</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+5</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Slayer Advance</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">10th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+10</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+5</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+5</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">3rd Studied Target, Slayer Talent, Sneak Attack +4d6</td></tr></tbody></table><p><br>The following are class features of the slayer prestige class.</p><p><strong>Weapon and Armor Proficiency:</strong> A slayer is proficient with all simple and martial weapons, as well as with light armor, medium armor, and shields (except tower shields).</p><p><strong>Studied Target (Ex):</strong> A slayer can study an opponent he can see as a move action. The slayer then gains a +1 bonus on Bluff, Knowledge, Perception, Sense Motive, and Survival checks attempted against that opponent, and a +1 bonus on weapon attack and damage rolls against it. The DCs of slayer class abilities against that opponent increase by 1. A slayer can only maintain these bonuses against one opponent at a time; these bonuses remain in effect until either the opponent is dead or the slayer studies a new target. If his studied target is also a favored enemy, these bonus stack.</p><p>If a slayer deals sneak attack damage to a target, he can study that target as an immediate action, allowing him to apply his studied target bonuses against that target (including to the normal weapon damage roll).</p><p>At 5th, and 10th levels, the bonuses on weapon attack, damage rolls, and skill checks and to slayer DCs against a studied target increase by 1. In addition, at each such interval, the slayer is able to maintain these bonuses against an additional studied target at the same time. The slayer may discard this connection to a studied target as a free action, allowing him to study another target in its place.</p><p>At 3rd level, a slayer can study an opponent as a move or swift action.</p><p><strong>Slayer Talents:</strong> As a slayer gains experience, he learns a number of talents that aid him and confound his foes. Starting at 2nd level and every 2 levels thereafter, a slayer gains one slayer talent. Unless otherwise noted, a slayer cannot select an individual talent more than once. Talents marked with an asterisk add effects to a slayer's sneak attack. Only one of these talents can be applied to an individual attack, and the decision of which to use must be made before the attack roll is made.</p><p><strong>Sneak Attack:</strong> At 2nd level, a slayer gains sneak attack as per the rogue ability. Initially, the extra damage dealt is 1d6, and it increases by 1d6 at 4th level, 7th level, and at 9th level. If a slayer gains a sneak attack bonus from another source, the bonuses on damage stack.</p><p><strong>Stalker (Ex):</strong> At 3rd level, a slayer gains his studied target bonus on Disguise, Intimidate, and Stealth checks against his studied opponent.</p><p><strong>Slayer's Advance (Ex):</strong> At 7th level, a slayer can once per day move up to twice his base speed as a move action. He may use Stealth as part of this movement, but takes a –10 penalty to his check for doing so. A slayer can use this ability a number of times per day equal to 3 plus his Intelligence modifier.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"links":{"children":[],"classAssociations":[{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.TPJgTOe2hvKpREKl","dataType":"compendium","name":"Slayer Talents (PRC)","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/featsfeatures/berserkFury.png","level":1,"_index":0},{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.hiaxKPsU9ttWwmBv","dataType":"compendium","name":"Slayer's Advance (PRC)","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/featsfeatures/flashStep.jpg","level":9,"_index":1},{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.mYbWHWemSsEkObnZ","dataType":"compendium","name":"Sneak Attack (PRC)","img":"systems/pf1/icons/skills/red_13.jpg","level":2,"_index":2},{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.k2GFu2Xv6OQcCWfp","dataType":"compendium","name":"Stalker (PRC)","img":"systems/pf1/icons/feats/stealthy.jpg","level":3,"_index":3},{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.Th1L5G5xCjyHNbdR","dataType":"compendium","name":"Studied Target (PRC)","img":"systems/pf1/icons/feats/tiring-critical.jpg","level":2,"_index":4}]},"tag":"slayer","useCustomTag":true,"armorProf":{"value":["lgt","med","shl"],"custom":""},"weaponProf":{"value":["sim","mar"],"custom":""},"languages":{"value":[],"custom":""},"flags":{"boolean":{},"dictionary":{"source":"Advanced Class Guide pg. 53, Modified","source_type":"class"}},"scriptCalls":[],"classType":"prestige","level":1,"hd":10,"hp":10,"bab":"high","skillsPerLevel":6,"savingThrows":{"fort":{"value":"high"},"ref":{"value":"high"},"will":{"value":"low"}},"fc":{"hp":{"value":0},"skill":{"value":0},"alt":{"value":0,"notes":""}},"classSkills":{"acr":true,"apr":false,"art":true,"blf":true,"clm":true,"crf":true,"dip":false,"dev":false,"dis":true,"esc":false,"fly":false,"han":false,"hea":true,"int":true,"kar":false,"kdu":true,"ken":false,"kge":true,"khi":false,"klo":true,"kna":false,"kno":false,"kpl":false,"kre":false,"lin":false,"lor":true,"per":true,"prf":false,"pro":true,"rid":true,"sen":true,"slt":false,"spl":false,"ste":true,"sur":true,"swm":true,"umd":false},"customHD":"","identifiedName":"Slayer (PrC)"},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"mBowgFU95wMOchUO":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf1","systemVersion":"0.82.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685519275483,"modifiedTime":1685608115621,"lastModifiedBy":"mBowgFU95wMOchUO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"0KfA6v0IVr3PWPMG"}
{"name":"Duelist (PrC)","type":"class","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/classesraces/duelist.png","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf1e-archetypes.pf-prestige-classes.xF0XWrJxRtdn96Hp"},"scene-packer":{"hash":"7f71a38e754c117fb96d8991cdfb19a65740e4d0","sourceId":"Item.vnk8EworwcQzMREU"},"pf1":{"links":{"classAssociations":{"g2rc4pyZ7PxqkBBB":1,"Pr1OZ4mgAlMoWeCf":1}}}},"system":{"description":{"value":"<h1 class=\"title\">Duelist</h1><p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\">In a world with heavily armored knights on huge, galloping chargers and powerful mages wielding mind-churning spells, there's no place for the daring swashbuckler who relies on his wits and reflexes to survive, right? Wrong. The duelist proves that precision and skill are viable alternatives to massive weapons and agility is a viable alternative to heavy armor.</span></p><p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\">The duelist is a nimble, intelligent fighter trained in making precise attacks with light weapons, such as the rapier. Also known as the swashbuckler, the duelist always takes full advantage of his quick reflexes and wits in a fight. Rather than wearing bulky armor, duelists feel the best way to protect themselves is to not get hit at all.</span></p><p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\">Duelists are most often fighters or rangers, but almost as often are rogues or bards. Wizards, sorcerers and monks make surprisingly good duelists due to the lack of the class's reliance on armor. They benefit greatly from the weapon skill the duelist offers. Paladins and barbarians who deviate a good deal from their archetypes become duelists. Elves are more likely to become duelists than dwarves, and halfling and gnome duelists are not uncommon. Half-orc duelists are very rare.</span></p><h2 class=\"title\">Requirements</h2><p>To qualify to become an duelist, a character must fulfill the following criteria.<br><br><strong>Feats</strong>: Dazzling Display, Exotic Weapon Proficiency (dueling sword), Weapon Finesse, Weapon Focus (dueling sword). <br><strong>Skills</strong>: Acrobatics 3 ranks, Intimidate 5 ranks, Sense Motive 3 ranks.</p><h2 class=\"title\">Class Skills</h2><p>The Duelist's class skills are Acrobatics (Dex), Bluff (Cha), Diplomacy (Cha), Escape Artist (Dex), Intimidate (Cha), Perform (Cha), and Sense Motive (Wis).<br><br><strong>Skill Points at each Level</strong>: 2 + Int modifier.<br><strong>Hit Die</strong>: d10.</p><h2 class=\"title\">Class Features</h2><table class=\"inner\" style=\"width: 96.9314%;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\"><strong>Level</strong></td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\"><strong>Base Attack Bonus</strong></td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\"><strong>Fort Save</strong></td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\"><strong>Ref Save</strong></td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\"><strong>Will Save</strong></td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\"><strong>Special</strong></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">1st</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+0</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+0</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Deft strike, quick draw</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">2nd</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Display weapon prowess</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">3rd</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Defensive parry +1</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">4th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+4</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Adaptive tactics 1</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">5th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+5</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Shatter confidence</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">6th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+6</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Saving slash</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">7th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+7</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+4</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Defensive parry +2, dexterous duelist</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">8th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+8</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+4</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Adaptive tactics 2</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">9th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+9</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+5</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Greater saving slash</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">10th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+10</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+5</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Confounding duelist</td></tr></tbody></table><p><br>The following are class features of the duelist prestige class. Unless stated otherwise, the following benefits apply only when a duelist is wielding a dueling sword (see page 24) and carrying nothing in his other hand.<br><br><strong>Deft Strike (Ex)</strong>: An duelist can add his Dexterity bonus (if any) to damage rolls made with an dueling sword instead of his Strength bonus. This bonus on damage rolls applies whether the duelist is wielding an dueling sword one-handed or two-handed. A duelist cannot use this ability if he is wielding a shield or using an off-hand weapon (including armor spikes, unarmed strikes, or natural weapons).</p><p><strong>Quick Draw</strong>: A duelist gains Quick Draw as a bonus feat. If the character already has this feat, he instead gains Dueling Mastery. If he already has both feats, he instead gains a combat feat of his choice as a bonus feat. The duelist must meet all prerequisites of the selected combat feat.</p><p><strong>Display Weapon Prowess (Ex)</strong>: At 2nd level, a duelist adds a bonus equal to half his class level on Intimidate checks while using Dazzling Display with a dueling sword. He also gains an additional +1 bonus on these Intimidate checks for each of the following feats he has with the dueling sword: Greater Weapon Focus, Greater Weapon Specialization, Improved Critical, Weapon Focus, or Weapon Specialization. The bonuses stack with each other (the total bonus is considered a competence bonus).</p><p>When involved in a duel, an duelist’s mastery of elaborate strikes and stances grants him a bonus equal to half his class level on performance combat checks. These tricks can also be of great help in countering an enemy during a duel, granting him a bonus equal to half his class level on rolls to attempt a dueling parry or to use dueling resolve.</p><p><strong>Defensive Parry (Ex)</strong>: At 3rd level, a duelist gains a +1 dodge bonus to his AC when making a full attack with an dueling sword. This AC bonus increases to +2 at 7th level. If an duelist is also a fighter with the defender fighter archetype, levels in this class stack with his fighter levels when determining the AC bonus from this ability.</p><p><strong>Adaptive Tactics (Ex)</strong>: At 4th level, an duelist learns to adapt his fighting style to counter his enemy’s strengths. A duelist reduces the attack roll penalty for fighting defensively or using Combat Expertise by 1 at 4th level and by 2 at 8th level. In addition, after an duelist uses his dueling sword to attack a creature he attacked during the previous round, as a swift action he can attempt a Sense Motive check (DC = 10 + the opponent’s base attack bonus). If successful, the duelist gains a +2 circumstance bonus either on attack rolls or to his AC against that creature until the beginning of his next turn.</p><p><strong>Shatter Confidence (Ex)</strong>: At 5th level, a duelist can attempt an Intimidate check to demoralize his target as a swift action after he confirms a critical hit or succeeds at a disarm, reposition, or sunder combat maneuver with an dueling sword. If his target is already shaken, the duelist can attempt an Intimidate check to demoralize the target as a swift action after any successful melee attack or combat maneuver. If he succeeds at this check, any morale bonuses the target has are suppressed for a number of rounds equal to the duelist’s class level. Suppressed effects are not dispelled, and they resume after this time elapses if their duration has not expired. Suppressed morale bonuses include those gained from a barbarian’s rage ability; however, this ability doesn’t end rage, nor does it suppress other effects of rage or rage powers that do not provide morale bonuses (thus, it doesn’t cause a barbarian to become fatigued unless the barbarian chooses to end the rage during the suppressed duration, in which case fatigue from rage affects the barbarian normally).</p><p><strong>Saving Slash (Ex)</strong>: At 6th level, when wielding an dueling sword, an duelist can use an immediate action to try deflecting a melee critical hit targeting him, reducing its damage to that of a normal hit, with a 25% chance of success. This does not stack with the fortification special ability of magical armor or similar effects.</p><p><strong>Dexterous Duelist (Ex)</strong>: At 7th level, a duelist with at least one free hand is not denied his Dexterity bonus when attempting Acrobatics or Climb checks, nor does he provoke attacks of opportunity when standing up from prone.</p><p><strong>Greater Saving Slash</strong>: At 9th level, a duelist’s saving slash has a 50% chance of reducing a melee critical hit to a normal hit. In addition, he can attempt a saving slash against ranged critical hits, including those from rays and other ranged touch effects, with a 25% chance of success.</p><p><strong>Confounding Duelist (Ex)</strong>: At 10th level, a duelist who successfully uses shatter confidence also suppresses the target’s competence and insight bonuses.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":["Prestige Class"],"changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false},"links":{"children":[],"classAssociations":[{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.o0YNQEAh2R1Wddx8","dataType":"compendium","name":"Adaptive Tactics (PRC)","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/midjourney/parry-002.png","level":4,"_index":0},{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.2IwXWchJjOsN3YpP","dataType":"compendium","name":"Confounding Duelist (PRC)","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/midjourney/aura-002.png","level":10,"_index":1},{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.cU9lRW20XQY2iaZm","dataType":"compendium","name":"Defensive Parry (PRC)","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/midjourney/parry-001.png","level":3,"_index":2},{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.2Zi49qF9J83DPeEn","dataType":"compendium","name":"Deft Strike (PRC)","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/midjourney/mid-0063.png","level":1,"_index":3},{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.uDu1t6pryyNYOJn0","dataType":"compendium","name":"Dexterous Duelist (PRC)","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/midjourney/dexterousDuelist.png","level":7,"_index":4},{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.4SIh0efr49Kv77aA","dataType":"compendium","name":"Display Weapon Prowess (PRC)","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/spells/enhancedWeapon.jpg","level":2,"_index":5},{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.srWIRYei5haIRem8","dataType":"compendium","name":"Greater Saving Slash (PRC)","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/midjourney/parry-003.png","level":9,"_index":6},{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.K76RPnMAr8LYT4qw","dataType":"compendium","name":"Quick Draw (PRC)","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/spells/Grace.png","level":1,"_index":7},{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.Jcn1Ni0ZNxyBFYcy","dataType":"compendium","name":"Saving Slash (PRC)","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/midjourney/parry-004.png","level":6,"_index":8},{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.pCbTGLiVWkINNDB5","dataType":"compendium","name":"Shatter Confidence (PRC)","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/midjourney/aura-001.png","level":5,"_index":9}]},"tag":"duelist","useCustomTag":true,"armorProf":{"value":[],"custom":""},"weaponProf":{"value":[],"custom":""},"languages":{"value":[],"custom":""},"flags":{"boolean":{},"dictionary":{"source":"Adventurer's Guide pg. 20, Paths of Prestige pg. 4","source_type":"class"}},"scriptCalls":[],"classType":"prestige","level":1,"hd":10,"hp":6,"bab":"high","skillsPerLevel":2,"savingThrows":{"fort":{"value":"low"},"ref":{"value":"high"},"will":{"value":"low"}},"fc":{"hp":{"value":0},"skill":{"value":0},"alt":{"value":0,"notes":""}},"classSkills":{"acr":true,"apr":false,"art":false,"blf":true,"clm":false,"crf":false,"dip":true,"dev":false,"dis":false,"esc":true,"fly":false,"han":false,"hea":false,"int":true,"kar":false,"kdu":false,"ken":false,"kge":false,"khi":false,"klo":false,"kna":fals