 word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; text-align: start\"><span style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Weapon and Armor Proficiency</strong>: Assassins are proficient with the crossbow (hand, light, or heavy), dagger (any type), dart, rapier, sap, shortbow (normal and composite), and short sword. Assassins are proficient with light armor but not with shields.</span></p><p><strong>Assassin Talents:</strong> As an assassin gains experience, she learns a number of talents that make her a more dangerous killer. <span style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif\">Starting at 1st level and every 2 levels thereafter, an assassin gains one assassin talent she meets the prerequisites for. Unless otherwise noted, an assassin cannot select an individual talent more than once. </span></p><p>Some talents are restricted by special abilities or class abilities possessed by a class or classes the assassin belonged to previously, such as spellcasting. Some assassin talents are more useful to those who belonged to a particular class, but an assassin may choose any talent so long as she meets its prerequisites.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(25, 24, 19); font-family: Signika, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; text-align: start\"><span style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif\">Talents marked with an asterisk add effects to an assassin’s sneak attack. Only one of these talents can be applied to an individual attack and the decision must be made before the attack roll is made. </span></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(25, 24, 19); font-family: Signika, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; text-align: start\"><span style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Sneak Attack</strong>: At 2nd level, an assassin gains sneak attack as per the rogue ability. Initially, the extra damage dealt is 1d6, and it increases by 1d6 at 4th level. If an assassin gains a sneak attack bonus from another source, the bonuses on damage stack.</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(25, 24, 19); font-family: Signika, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; text-align: start\"></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"links":{"children":[],"classAssociations":[{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.C2vebsnqKoY0MBCq","dataType":"compendium","name":"Angel of Death (PRC)","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/featsfeatures/grimHarvest.png","level":5,"_index":0},{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class