{"name":"Slayer (PrC)","type":"class","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/classesraces/slayer.png","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf1.classes.cOY76lMUkupH534m"},"scene-packer":{"hash":"c2f750f900dc8f363407aa5e4ce19c4ed6dba294","sourceId":"Item.omQz6bA65rjFR3Vy"}},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Skilled at tracking down targets, slayers are consummate hunters, living for the chase and the deadly stroke that brings it to a close. Slayers spend most of their time honing their weapon skills, studying the habits and anatomy of foes, and practicing combat maneuvers.</p><p><strong>Role</strong>: The slayer is elusive, and good at finding the opportune time and location to strike. Combining the deadliest talents of rangers and rogues, a slayer’s abilities are all about getting into combat, dealing with a target, and then getting back out again.</p><h2 class=\"title\">Requirements</h2><p>To qualify to become an duelist, a character must fulfill the following criteria.<br><br><strong>Base Attack Bonus:</strong> +4<br><strong>Skills</strong>: Knowledge (Nature) 3 ranks, Stealth 5 ranks, and Survival 4 ranks.<br><strong>Special:</strong> Favored Enemy class feature and Sneak Attack +2d6.</p><h2><span id=\"Class_Skills\">Class Skills</span></h2><p>The slayer’s class skills are <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/acrobatics\">Acrobatics</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Dexterity-Dex-\">Dex</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/bluff\">Bluff</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Charisma-Cha-\">Cha</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/climb\">Climb</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Strength-Str-\">Str</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/craft\">Craft</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Int</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/disguise\">Disguise</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Charisma-Cha-\">Cha</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/heal\">Heal</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Wisdom-Wis-\">Wis</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/intimidate\">Intimidate</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Charisma-Cha-\">Cha</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/knowledge\">Knowledge</a> (dungeoneering) (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Int</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/knowledge\">Knowledge</a> (geography) (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Int</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/knowledge\">Knowledge</a> (local) (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Int</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/perception\">Perception</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Wisdom-Wis-\">Wis</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/profession\">Profession</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Wisdom-Wis-\">Wis</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/ride\">Ride</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Dexterity-Dex-\">Dex</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/sense-motive\">Sense Motive</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Wisdom-Wis-\">Wis</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/stealth\">Stealth</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Dexterity-Dex-\">Dex</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/survival\">Survival</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Wisdom-Wis-\">Wis</a>), and <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/swim\">Swim</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Strength-Str-\">Str</a>).</p><p><strong>Skill Ranks per Level</strong>: 6 + <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Int</a> <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Determine-Bonuses\">modifier</a>.<br><strong>Hit Die</strong>: d10.</p><h2 class=\"title\">Class Features</h2><table class=\"inner\" style=\"width: 96.9314%;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\"><strong>Level</strong></td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\"><strong>Base Attack Bonus</strong></td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\"><strong>Fort Save</strong></td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\"><strong>Ref Save</strong></td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\"><strong>Will Save</strong></td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\"><strong>Special</strong></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">1st</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+0</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Studied Target</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">2nd</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Slayer Talent, Sneak Attack +1d6</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">3rd</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Stalker</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">4th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+4</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Slayer Talent, Sneak Attack +2d6</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">5th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+5</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">2nd Studied Target</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">6th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+6</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Advanced Talents, Slayer Talent</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">7th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+7</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+4</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+4</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Sneak Attack +3d6</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">8th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+8</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+4</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+4</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Slayer Talent</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">9th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+9</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+5</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+5</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">Slayer Advance</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 10.5744%;\">10th</td><td style=\"width: 16.6137%;\">+10</td><td style=\"width: 10.8007%;\">+5</td><td style=\"width: 9.68343%;\">+5</td><td style=\"width: 10.6145%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 41.3408%;\">3rd Studied Target, Slayer Talent, Sneak Attack +4d6</td></tr></tbody></table><p><br>The following are class features of the slayer prestige class.</p><p><strong>Weapon and Armor Proficiency:</strong> A slayer is proficient with all simple and martial weapons, as well as with light armor, medium armor, and shields (except tower shields).</p><p><strong>Studied Target (Ex):</strong> A slayer can study an opponent he can see as a move action. The slayer then gains a +1 bonus on Bluff, Knowledge, Perception, Sense Motive, and Survival checks attempted against that opponent, and a +1 bonus on weapon attack and damage rolls against it. The DCs of slayer class abilities against that opponent increase by 1. A slayer can only maintain these bonuses against one opponent at a time; these bonuses remain in effect until either the opponent is dead or the slayer studies a new target. If his studied target is also a favored enemy, these bonus stack.</p><p>If a slayer deals sneak attack damage to a target, he can study that target as an immediate action, allowing him to apply his studied target bonuses against that target (including to the normal weapon damage roll).</p><p>At 5th, and 10th levels, the bonuses on weapon attack, damage rolls, and skill checks and to slayer DCs against a studied target increase by 1. In addition, at each such interval, the slayer is able to maintain these bonuses against an additional studied target at the same time. The slayer may discard this connection to a studied target as a free action, allowing him to study another target in its place.</p><p>At 3rd level, a slayer can study an opponent as a move or swift action.</p><p><strong>Slayer Talents:</strong> As a slayer gains experience, he learns a number of talents that aid him and confound his foes. Starting at 2nd level and every 2 levels thereafter, a slayer gains one slayer talent. Unless otherwise noted, a slayer cannot select an individual talent more than once. Talents marked with an asterisk add effects to a slayer's sneak attack. Only one of these talents can be applied to an individual attack, and the decision of which to use must be made before the attack roll is made.</p><p><strong>Sneak Attack:</strong> At 2nd level, a slayer gains sneak attack as per the rogue ability. Initially, the extra damage dealt is 1d6, and it increases by 1d6 at 4th level, 7th level, and at 9th level. If a slayer gains a sneak attack bonus from another source, the bonuses on damage stack.</p><p><strong>Stalker (Ex):</strong> At 3rd level, a slayer gains his studied target bonus on Disguise, Intimidate, and Stealth checks against his studied opponent.</p><p><strong>Slayer's Advance (Ex):</strong> At 7th level, a slayer can once per day move up to twice his base speed as a move action. He may use Stealth as part of this movement, but takes a –10 penalty to his check for doing so. A slayer can use this ability a number of times per day equal to 3 plus his Intelligence modifier.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"links":{"children":[],"classAssociations":[{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.TPJgTOe2hvKpREKl","dataType":"compendium","name":"Slayer Talents (PRC)","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/featsfeatures/berserkFury.png","level":1,"_index":0},{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.hiaxKPsU9ttWwmBv","dataType":"compendium","name":"Slayer's Advance (PRC)","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/featsfeatures/flashStep.jpg","level":9,"_index":1},{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.mYbWHWemSsEkObnZ","dataType":"compendium","name":"Sneak Attack (PRC)","img":"systems/pf1/icons/skills/red_13.jpg","level":2,"_index":2},{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.k2GFu2Xv6OQcCWfp","dataType":"compendium","name":"Stalker (PRC)","img":"systems/pf1/icons/feats/stealthy.jpg","level":3,"_index":3},{"id":"greyhawk-pathfinder-1e.Greyhawk-Class-Features.Th1L5G5xCjyHNbdR","dataType":"compendium","name":"Studied Target (PRC)","img":"systems/pf1/icons/feats/tiring-critical.jpg","level":2,"_index":4}]},"tag":"slayer","useCustomTag":true,"armorProf":{"value":["lgt","med","shl"],"custom":""},"weaponProf":{"value":["sim","mar"],"custom":""},"languages":{"value":[],"custom":""},"flags":{"boolean":{},"dictionary":{"source":"Advanced Class Guide pg. 53, Modified","source_type":"class"}},"scriptCalls":[],"classType":"prestige","level":1,"hd":10,"hp":10,"bab":"high","skillsPerLevel":6,"savingThrows":{"fort":{"value":"high"},"ref":{"value":"high"},"will":{"value":"low"}},"fc":{"hp":{"value":0},"skill":{"value":0},"alt":{"value":0,"notes":""}},"classSkills":{"acr":true,"apr":false,"art":true,"blf":true,"clm":true,"crf":true,"dip":false,"dev":false,"dis":true,"esc":false,"fly":false,"han":false,"hea":true,"int":true,"kar":false,"kdu":true,"ken":false,"kge":true,"khi":false,"klo":true,"kna":false,"kno":false,"kpl":false,"kre":false,"lin":false,"lor":true,"per":true,"prf":false,"pro":true,"rid":true,"sen":true,"slt":false,"spl":false,"ste":true,"sur":true,"swm":true,"umd":false},"customHD":"","identifiedName":"Slayer (PrC)"},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"mBowgFU95wMOchUO":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf1","systemVersion":"0.82.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685519275483,"modifiedTime":1686030892240,"lastModifiedBy":"mBowgFU95wMOchUO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"0KfA6v0IVr3PWPMG"}
{"name":"Bloodrager (PrC) - Temp","type":"class","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/classesraces/bloodrager.png","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf1.classes.cOY76lMUkupH534m"},"scene-packer":{"hash":"fb257f5a8b8cfa9ce0c6386d85778738ad6f7787","sourceId":"Item.YkBVDGOVGDKDABlL"}},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif\">While many ferocious combatants can tap into a deep reservoir of buried rage, bloodragers have an intrinsic power that seethes within. Like sorcerers, bloodragers’ veins surge with arcane power. While sorcerers use this power for spellcasting, bloodragers enter an altered state in which their bloodline becomes manifest, where the echoes of their strange ancestry lash out with devastating power. In these states, bloodragers can cast some arcane spells instinctively. The bloodrager’s magic is as fast, violent, and seemingly unstoppable as their physical prowess.</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(25, 24, 19); font-family: Signika, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; text-align: start\"><span style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Role</strong>: Masters of the battlefield, bloodragers unleash fearful carnage on their enemies using their bloodlines and combat prowess. The bloodrager’s place is on the front lines, right in his enemies’ faces, supplying tremendous martial force bolstered by a trace of arcane magic.</span></p><h2 class=\"title\">Requirements</h2><p>To qualify to become an bloodrager, a character must fulfill the following criteria.</p><p><strong>Base Attack Bonus:</strong> +4<br><strong>Skills</strong>: .<br><strong>Special:</strong> Rage class feature, and ability to cast 1st-level arcane spells without preparation. If the character has sorcerer levels, he must have access to a bloodline. If the character gains levels of sorcerer after taking this class, he must not take any archetype that replaces his bloodline,</p><h2><span id=\"Class_Skills\">Class Skills</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif\">The bloodrager’s class skills are <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/acrobatics\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Acrobatics</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Dexterity-Dex-\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Dex</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/climb\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Climb</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Strength-Str-\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Str</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/craft\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Craft</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Int</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/handle-animal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Handle Animal</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Charisma-Cha-\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Cha</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/intimidate\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Intimidate</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Charisma-Cha-\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Cha</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/knowledge\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Knowledge</a> (arcana) (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Int</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/perception\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Perception</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Wisdom-Wis-\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Wis</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/ride\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Ride</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Dexterity-Dex-\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Dex</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/spellcraft\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Spellcraft</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Int</a>), <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/survival\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Survival</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Wisdom-Wis-\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Wis</a>), and <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/swim\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Swim</a> (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Strength-Str-\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Str</a>).</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(25, 24, 19); font-family: Signika, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; text-align: start\"><span style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Skill Ranks per Level</strong>: 4 + <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; cursor: pointer; color: var(--color-text-hyperlink);\">Int</a> modifier.<br><strong>Hit Die</strong>: d10.</span></p><h2 class=\"title\">Class Features</h2><table class=\"inner\" style=\"width: 96.9314%;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"width: 8%;\"><strong>Level</strong></td><td style=\"width: 16%;\"><strong>Base Attack Bonus</strong></td><td style=\"width: 8%;\"><strong>Fort Save</strong></td><td style=\"width: 8%;\"><strong>Ref Save</strong></td><td style=\"width: 8%;\"><strong>Will Save</strong></td><td style=\"width: 26%;\"><strong>Special</strong></td><td style=\"width: 26%;\"><strong>Spells Per Day</strong></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 8%;\">1st</td><td style=\"width: 16%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+0</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+0</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">Bloodrage, deviant bloodline</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">---</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 8%;\">2nd</td><td style=\"width: 16%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">Blood sanctuary</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">+1 level of spontaneous arcane spellcasting class</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 8%;\">3rd</td><td style=\"width: 16%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">Rage power</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">+1 level of spontaneous arcane spellcasting class</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 8%;\">4th</td><td style=\"width: 16%;\">+4</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+1</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">Blood casting</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">+1 level of spontaneous arcane spellcasting class</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 8%;\">5th</td><td style=\"width: 16%;\">+5</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">Damage reduction 1 / - [???]</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">+1 level of spontaneous arcane spellcasting class</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 8%;\">6th</td><td style=\"width: 16%;\">+5</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">Rage power</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">---</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 8%;\">7th</td><td style=\"width: 16%;\">+7</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+4</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+2</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">Greater bloodrage</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">+1 level of spontaneous arcane spellcasting class</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 8%;\">8th</td><td style=\"width: 16%;\">+8</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+4</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">Indomitable will</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">+1 level of spontaneous arcane spellcasting class</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 8%;\">9th</td><td style=\"width: 16%;\">+9</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+5</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">Rage power</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">+1 level of spontaneous arcane spellcasting class</td></tr><tr><td style=\"width: 8%;\">10th</td><td style=\"width: 16%;\">+10</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+5</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 8%;\">+3</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">Tireless bloodrage</td><td style=\"width: 26%;\">+1 level of spontaneous arcane spellcasting class</td></tr></tbody></table><p><br>The following are class features of the bloodrager prestige class.</p><p><strong>Weapon and Armor Proficiency:</strong> A bloodrager is proficient with all simple and martial weapons, as well as with light armor, medium armor, and shields (except tower shields). A bloodrager can spontaneously cast arcane spells while wearing light armor or medium armor without incurring the normal arcane spell failure chance. This does not affect the arcane spell failure chance for prepared arcane spells. Like other arcane spellcasters, a bloodrager wearing heavy armor or wielding a shield incurs a chance of arcane spell failure if the spell in question has somatic components.</p><p><strong>Bloodrage (Su):</strong> A</p><p><strong>Blood Sanctuary (Su):</strong> At 3rd level, due to the power of his blood, a bloodrager can stand confidently amid the effects of spells cast by himself or his allies. He gains a +2 bonus on saving throws against spells that he or an ally casts.</p><p><strong>Rage Power:</strong> S</p><p><strong>Blood Casting (Su):</strong> At 4th level, the bloodrager gains the ability to cast spells even while bloodraging. He can also cast these spells defensively and can make concentration checks for these spells while bloodraging. While bloodraging, he can cast and concentrate on only his bloodrager spells (see below); spells from other classes cannot be cast during this state.</p><p><strong>Damage Reduction (Ex):</strong> At 7th level, a bloodrager gains damage reduction. Subtract 1 from the damage the bloodrager takes each time he is dealt damage from a weapon or a natural attack. At 10th level, and every 3 levels thereafter, this damage reduction increases by 1 point. Damage reduction can reduce damage to 0, but not below 0.</p><p><strong>Greater Bloodrage (Su):</strong> At 11th level, when a bloodrager enters a bloodrage, the morale bonus to his Strength and Constitution increases to +6 and the morale bonus on his Will saves increases to +3. In addition, upon entering a bloodrage, the bloodrager can apply the effects a bloodrager spell he knows of 2nd level or lower to himself. The spell must have a range of touch or personal. If the spell’s duration is greater than 1 round, it instead lasts for the duration of the bloodrage. This use consumes a bloodrager spell slot, as if he had cast the spell; he must have the spell slot available to take advantage of this effect.</p><p>Greater bloodrage counts as the barbarian’s greater rage ability for the purposes of feat prerequisites, feat abilities, magic item abilities, and spell effects.</p><p><strong>Indomitable Will (Ex):</strong> At 14th level, a bloodrager gains a +4 bonus on Will saves to resist enchantment spells while bloodraging. This bonus stacks with all other modifiers, including the morale bonus on Will saves he also receives during his bloodrage.</p><p><strong>Tireless Bloodrage (Su):</strong> At 17th level, a bloodrager no longer becomes fatigued at the end of his bloodrage.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"links":{"children":[],"classAssociations":[]},"tag":"slayer","useCustomTag":true,"armorProf":{"value":["lgt","med","shl"],"custom":""},"weaponProf":{"value":["sim","mar"],"custom":""},"languages":{"value":[],"custom":""},"flags":{"boolean":{},"dictionary":{"source":"Advanced Class Guide pg. 53, Modified","source_type":"class"}},"scriptCalls":[],"classType":"prestige","level":1,"hd":10,"hp":10,"bab":"high","skillsPerLevel":6,"savingThrows":{"fort":{"value":"high"},"ref":{"value":"high"},"will":{"value":"low"}},"fc":{"hp":{"value":0},"skill":{"value":0},"alt":{"value":0,"notes":""}},"classSkills":{"acr":true,"apr":false,"art":true,"blf":true,"clm":true,"crf":true,"dip":false,"dev":false,"dis":true,"esc":false,"fly":false,"han":false,"hea":true,"int":true,"kar":false,"kdu":true,"ken":false,"kge":true,"khi":false,"klo":true,"kna":false,"kno":false,"kpl":false,"kre":false,"lin":false,"lor":true,"per":true,"prf":false,"pro":true,"rid":true,"sen":true,"slt":false,"spl":false,"ste":true,"sur":true,"swm":true,"umd":false},"customHD":"","identifiedName":"Bloodrager (PrC) - Temp"},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"mBowgFU95wMOchUO":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf1","systemVersion":"0.82.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685519275483,"modifiedTime":1686041892425,"lastModifiedBy":"mBowgFU95wMOchUO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"LhaeuKrLacTuqJBI"}
